LAFIA – Nasarawa State chapter of the Young Progress Party (YPP), on Sunday preached against money bag politics, saying if Nigerian didn’t desist from money bag politics the essence of not too young to run bill recently accented by Mr. President has been defeated. The party also expressed readiness to receive aggrieved defectors from the ruling All Progress Congress (APC), and opposition People’s Democratic Party (PDP), to the party. Honourable Bishop Mathew, disclosed this while answering questions DAILY INDEPENDENT in Lafia the state capital. -Advertisement- Mathew, said the have had a successful Primaries in the state that will enable YPP to participate in the 2023 election. According to YPP chairman,” If you want to participate in an election you dose not need big political party to showcase your popularity, we want young people to look beyond PDP and APC because there are big fish who would not allow the young people to contest because the house can’t accommodate everybody. ” Is not about APC neither about PDP is all about ideology. When you look at manifesto of YPP, is so unique to compare with any. “We are expecting defectors from our party we are working towards receiving them into our party, the reason is our political is not like other political,” he said. Bishop Mathew, also noted that the party is fully prepared for the general election come 2023, adding that the party is going to wins so many offices including governor in 2023. POLL He however said the Young Progress Party has come to change the narrative of Nasarawa State politics if given mandate come 2023.